===Etymology===
First coined 1935, from {{etyl|it}} {{term|lang=it|pizza}}, of uncertain origin, perhaps from {{etyl|gkm}} {{term|πίττα||cake, pie|tr=pitta|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|πίσσα||pitch|tr=pissa|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, [[Attic]] {{term|πίττα||tr=pitta|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, from {{term|πεπτός||cooked|tr=peptos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/piːtsə/}}
* {{audio|en-us-pizza.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl2=pizze|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} A [[baked]] [[Italian]] [[dish]] of a thinly rolled bread dough crust typically [[top]]ped before baking with [[tomato sauce]], [[cheese]]{{,}} and other ingredients.
#: ''a slice of '''pizza'''''
#: ''a [[pizza pie|'''pizza''' pie]]''
#: ''Want to go out for '''pizza''' tonight?''
# {{countable}} A baked thinly rolled bread dough crust typically [[top]]ped before baking with [[tomato sauce]], [[cheese]]{{,}} and other ingredients.
#: ''He ate a whole '''pizza'''!''

====Usage notes====
* In phrases like {{term||pizza bread}} and {{term||pizza bagel}}, {{term||pizza}} refers to the toppings: pizza bread is normal bread with pizza-like toppings.

